Summary: Two sightings-round amber orange colored object moving over Salt Lake City Valley.
divs: Sighting DetailsMarch 16th, 2009 at 8:20pm I spotted a star like object moving from the southern area of the sky. It was moving north. It was amber to orange in color. It was above the clouds. It moved into the clouds and came out from behind the clouds moving ENE direction and turned to the NE and disappeared at a distance. I took a picture with my 35mm camera with 800asa film. Camera lens zoomed at 105, aperture 4, speed 8���. We will have to see if I get a picture? I will need to develop the film. March 16th, 2009 at 8:40pm I spotted a star like object moving from the SW area towards me as it curved down then moved upward and leveled off moving NE. It was above the clouds and was amber to orange in color. At 8:48pm I saw a blue light defusing widely though the clouds. It was very fast and moving from north to south. At 9:10pm I saw a blue light once more quickly moving through the clouds in the same direction.
